bib_record.title: Isospin-forbidden particle decays in light nuclei (II). Widths of T =3/2 levels of 17O.

free_txt: The Chalk River MP Tandem accelerator
Three 5 cm long by 5 cm diameter NE213 liquid
scintillators coupled to RCA8575 photomultipliers.
Relative neutron efficiencies were determined from the
values tabulated by Verbinskii et al. presented
in Nucl.Instr.,65,8,1968 for neutron detectors of
approximately this geometry.
The Chalk River MP Tandem accelerator
Absolute cross sections were determined by normalizing
to the cross-section measurements of Kerr et al. in
the region of incident energy between 4.2 and 5.0 MeV.
The polymerized hydrocarbon targets
were prepared by cracking methyl iodide onto thick
tantalum backings by means of a radio-frequency
discharge induced by a tesla coil. Target thickness
ranged from 0.5 to 30 mu-g/cm2. Thickness for the
thickest targets was determined from the energy loss
of 5.48 MeV alpha-particles from an 241Am source.
Target thicknesses for the thinner targets were
determined from the relative yields of the
13C(alpha,n0) reaction.
No information on source of uncertainties.
Figs.3-6 in J,NP/A,273,464,1976 were
digitized by GSYS2.4.7.
